description:
SAP is throwing connection errors after we updated the config. Here's our config:

```json
{
  "connectionSettings": {
    "sapServer": "sap-prod-01.contoso.com",
    "sapPort": 3200,
    "sapClient": "100",
    "sapSystemNumber": "00",
    "sapLanguage": "EN",
    "connectionPool": {
      "maxConnections": 50,
      "minConnections": 5,
      "idleTimeout": 300,
      "connectionTimeout": 30
    },
    "retryPolicy": {
      "maxRetries": 3,
      "backoffMultiplier": 2.0,
      "initialDelay": 1000
    },
    "ssl": {
      "enabled": true,
      "certPath": "/etc/certs/sap-prod.pem",
      "verifyHostname": true
    }
  },
  "logging": {
    "level": "DEBUG",
    "outputPath": "/var/log/sap-connector/"
  },
  "features": {
    "batchProcessing": true,
    "asyncMode": false,
    "compressionEnabled": true,
    "cacheEnabled": true,
    "cacheTTL": 600
  }
}
```

The error is: 'RFC connection failed: CPIC-CALL: ThSAPCMRCV on connection timeout'. This started after we changed the connectionTimeout from 60 to 30. 20 users in Finance are unable to process month-end transactions.
